text:
4460-4466 Broadway at the N.E. corner of Fairview Avenue, between 190th and 192nd Streets.
About 1925.

General Photographic Company.

Broadway (street level not seen, being between buildings and hillock) at Fairview Avenue, as viewed from Wadsworth Terrace and across intervening roof tops. Shown atop the bluff are: the castlelike structure of Dr. Chas V. Paterno; the studio of Geo. Barnard Grey; and the mansion and estate of C.K.G. Billings. The latter is today part of Fort Tryon Park.

October 26, 1927.
Views 1 and 2

P.L. Sperr
